  <!-- Quick Start -->
  <section id="quick-start">
    <h2>Quick Start</h2>
    <p>Import the opt-in CSS utility. This single import gives you smooth crossfade transitions on all same-origin navigations:</p>

    {% set _code9 %}@import "vanilla-breeze/utils/view-transitions.css";{% endset %}
    <code-block language="css" label="Import view transitions">{{ _code9 | escape }}</code-block>

    <p>That&rsquo;s it for basic crossfade. The <code>&lt;main&gt;</code> element automatically gets a named transition group (<code>main-content</code>) so content fades smoothly between pages.</p>

    <p>For shared element morphing, add <code>data-vt-name</code> to elements that should animate between pages:</p>

    {% set _code8 %}<!-- Gallery page -->
<a href="/products/123">
  <img data-vt-name="product-123" src="thumb.jpg" />
  <h2 data-vt-name="title-123">Product Name</h2>
</a>

<!-- Detail page - matching names morph smoothly -->
<img data-vt-name="product-123" src="hero.jpg" />
<h1 data-vt-name="title-123">Product Name</h1>{% endset %}
    <code-block language="html" label="Shared element morphing">{{ _code8 | escape }}</code-block>

    <p>The <code>data-vt-name</code> attribute requires the init script (included in all doc site layouts, or import <code>view-transition-init.js</code>).</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Named Groups -->
  <section id="named-groups">
    <h2>Named Groups</h2>
    <p>Use <code>data-vt</code> to assign common transition names to page regions. Named elements persist or morph across navigations instead of crossfading.</p>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Transition Name</th>
          <th>Use Case</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>data-vt="main"</code></td><td><code>main-content</code></td><td>Main content area (auto-applied to <code>&lt;main&gt;</code>)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>data-vt="header"</code></td><td><code>page-header</code></td><td>Site header &mdash; persists across pages</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>data-vt="nav"</code></td><td><code>site-nav</code></td><td>Primary navigation</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>data-vt="sidebar"</code></td><td><code>page-sidebar</code></td><td>Sidebar navigation &mdash; stays in place within sections</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>data-vt="hero"</code></td><td><code>page-hero</code></td><td>Hero image or banner</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>data-vt="footer"</code></td><td><code>site-footer</code></td><td>Site footer</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    {% set _code7 %}<header data-vt="header">...</header>
<nav data-vt="sidebar">...</nav>
<main> <!-- auto-named as main-content -->
  <div data-vt="hero">...</div>
  ...
</main>
<footer data-vt="footer">...</footer>{% endset %}
    <code-block language="html" label="Named groups in layout">{{ _code7 | escape }}</code-block>

    <p>When navigating between pages with the same named group, the browser morphs the element in place rather than crossfading. This keeps headers, sidebars, and footers visually stable during navigation.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Shared Element Morphing -->
  <section id="shared-elements">
    <h2>Shared Element Morphing</h2>
    <p>For unique per-element names (galleries, product cards, lists), use <code>data-vt-name</code>:</p>

    {% set _code6 %}<!-- Each element gets a unique name -->
<img data-vt-name="hero-1" src="thumb-1.jpg" />
<img data-vt-name="hero-2" src="thumb-2.jpg" />
<img data-vt-name="hero-3" src="thumb-3.jpg" />

<!-- On the detail page, the matching name morphs -->
<img data-vt-name="hero-1" src="full-1.jpg" />{% endset %}
    <code-block language="html" label="data-vt-name usage">{{ _code6 | escape }}</code-block>

    <p>The init script (<code>view-transition-init.js</code>) sets <code>view-transition-name</code> from the attribute value. This replaces the need for inline <code>style</code> attributes.</p>

    <h3>How the Init Script Works</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>On <code>DOMContentLoaded</code>, discovers all <code>[data-vt-name]</code> elements</li>
      <li>Sets <code>el.style.viewTransitionName</code> from the attribute value</li>
      <li>Marks each element with <code>data-vt-name-init</code> to prevent double-processing</li>
      <li>A <code>MutationObserver</code> handles dynamically added elements</li>
    </ol>

    {% set _code5 %}// Already included in doc site layouts
// For standalone pages:
import 'vanilla-breeze/utils/view-transition-init.js';{% endset %}
    <code-block language="js" label="Import the init script">{{ _code5 | escape }}</code-block>

    <p><strong>Important:</strong> Each <code>view-transition-name</code> must be unique per page. Two elements with the same name on the same page will cause errors.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Animation Presets -->
  <section id="animation-presets">
    <h2>Animation Presets</h2>
    <p>Apply animation presets to transition groups using <code>data-vt-class</code>. This uses the CSS <code>view-transition-class</code> property to style transitions without targeting individual names.</p>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Value</th>
          <th>Effect</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>slide-left</code></td><td>Old content slides out left, new slides in from right</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>slide-right</code></td><td>Old content slides out right, new slides in from left</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>scale</code></td><td>Old content scales down and fades, new scales up</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>fade</code></td><td>Pure opacity crossfade (no morphing)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>none</code></td><td>Instant swap with no animation</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    {% set _code4 %}<!-- Slide main content from the left -->
<main data-vt-class="slide-left">...</main>

<!-- Scale the hero section -->
<div data-vt="hero" data-vt-class="scale">...</div>

<!-- No animation for footer -->
<footer data-vt="footer" data-vt-class="none">...</footer>{% endset %}
    <code-block language="html" label="Animation presets">{{ _code4 | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

