  <!-- MPA vs SPA -->
  <section id="mpa-vs-spa">
    <h2>MPA vs SPA</h2>

    <h3>Multi-Page Applications (MPA)</h3>
    <p>For traditional multi-page sites, use the CSS <code>@view-transition</code> rule. This is what the Vanilla Breeze utility provides:</p>

    {% set _code2 %}@view-transition {
  navigation: auto;
}{% endset %}
    <code-block language="css" label="MPA transitions">{{ _code2 | escape }}</code-block>

    <p>The browser automatically triggers transitions on same-origin navigations. No JavaScript needed.</p>

    <h3>Single-Page Applications (SPA)</h3>
    <p>For SPA routing (client-side navigation), use the JavaScript API:</p>

    {% set _code1 %}document.startViewTransition(() => {
  // Update the DOM here
  updateContent(newContent);
});{% endset %}
    <code-block language="js" label="SPA transitions">{{ _code1 | escape }}</code-block>

    <p>The same CSS transition names and animation presets work with both approaches.</p>
  </section>

